cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

This paper describes a dependency parsing system for the CoNLL2017 Shared Task, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses a framework called DRAGNN, which involves recurrent neural networks, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper uses character-based word representations, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper may also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it involves parsing and tagging of text data.
